conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Excuse me. Could I ask you some questions?

conversation.speaker: Jim
conversation.text: Oh, you're in class 6A, aren't you?

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Yes, that's right. My name's Jenny. I'm doing a survey for my geography class.

conversation.speaker: Jim
conversation.text: My name is Jim. What do you want to know?

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Thank you, Jim.

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Do you live in a house?

conversation.speaker: Jim
conversation.text: No, I don't. I live in an apartment.

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: How many bedrooms does it have?

conversation.speaker: Jim
conversation.text: Two.

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Does it have a pool?

conversation.speaker: Jim
conversation.text: Yes. A small one.

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Does it have a garage?

conversation.speaker: Jim
conversation.text: No, it doesn't.

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Does it have a gym?

conversation.speaker: Jim
conversation.text: Yes, it does. There's a gym in the basement.

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Does it have a balcony?

conversation.speaker: Jim
conversation.text: Yes, it does. I can see the city from it.

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Great. Thank you for your help.

conversation.speaker: Jim
conversation.text: You're welcome.

conversation.speaker: Jenny
conversation.text: Goodbye.
